{
  "stem": "11801.2",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "In any case, we were sent back to the orphanage.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "And this time, I went to a different unit, which was a little upsetting, since I had gotten used to this place.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "I mean, this was now my third stop.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "First in the first building, and then the-- the place in Middelkerke, where I did meet some Jewish children that I'm still friendly with.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "Well, we lost contact for many years, but we did find each other eventually.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "And went back and was moved twice.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "They-- I guess they were looking for the right spot.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "I have no idea.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "I came back from Middelkerke, went to a different place, and then went to a different building again.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "You can call the building, unit, if you like, where I stayed for the rest of the-- my stay in the orphanage, which lasted almost eight years.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "So I grew up there.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 7 SECONDS] Life in the orphanage [PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] was not bad.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "I never thought I had a bad experience in that orphanage.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "In terms of being taken care of, they looked after me as well as they looked after any of the children.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "There was no difference between a Jewish child and a non-Jewish child.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "The Belgians were very anti-German.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 44,
      "text": "They were not anti-Semitic.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 45,
      "text": "Nobody cared what I was Jewish.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 46,
      "text": "They did-- it did bother some that I was German though, which used to infuriate me, because being German was the last thing I wanted to be.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 47,
      "text": "And to be accused of being German, you know, in fights I might have had with other children, which I did have, to be called a-- you know, by some nasty word because I was German, used to, oh, boy, you know, I'd tear the kids' hair out.",
      "word_count": 48
    }
  ],
